article.headline: Pacific 76, Holy Names 38
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. -- Ross Rivera scored 14 points to lead Pacific to a 76-38 win over Holy Names on Saturday night in the season opener for both teams. Rivera was 2 of 2 from 3-point range and had seven rebounds. Tim Thomas and Travis Fulton had 10 points each. Colin Beatty also had seven rebounds for the Tigers. Pacific led 47-17 at halftime. Ian Collins led the Hawks with 10 points. Richard Craig, who had 6 points, was 2 of 5 from 3-point range. Tyler Fry had seven rebounds. Holy Names was 15-16 last season. The Hawks moved to Division II this season.
